**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Authentication Layer**: Multiple auth methods (JWT, API key, session) all verified server-side
```php
// Never trust tokens alone - always verify against database
$userRole = $this->getVerifiedRole($userId); // From DB, not token
```

2. **Authorization Layer**: Centralized permission checking before any business logic
```php
// Permission defined once, enforced everywhere
'users.update_role' => ['admin'],  // Only admins can change roles
```

3. **Business Logic Layer**: Additional constraints even after authorization passes
```php
// Can't assign roles at or above your own level
if ($roleHierarchy[$newRole] >= $roleHierarchy[$currentRole]) {
    return ['error' => 'Cannot assign this role level'];
}
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Session fingerprinting**: Prevents session hijacking by binding sessions to client characteristics
- **Rate limiting**: Add rate limits on sensitive endpoints to slow brute force attempts
- **Real-time alerting**: Immediate notification on privilege escalation attempts
- **Audit trail**: Complete log of all authorization decisions for forensics
- **Principle of least privilege**: Roles can only grant permissions below their own level
- **Fail-secure defaults**: Unknown permissions or roles result in denial
- **Input validation at every layer**: Don't trust any input, even from authenticated users

Role-based access control (RBAC) is critical for preventing privilege escalation attacks. A common vulnerability occurs when developers trust client-supplied role information or fail to verify roles server-side on every request.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```csharp
using System;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using System.Security.Claims;

namespace VulnerableApp.Controllers
{
    [ApiController]
    [Route("api/[controller]")]
    public class UserController : ControllerBase
    {
        private readonly IUserService _userService;

        public UserController(IUserService userService)
        {
            _userService = userService;
        }

        // VULNERABLE: Trusts client-supplied role in request body
        [HttpPost("update-user")]
        public IActionResult UpdateUser([FromBody] UserUpdateRequest request)
        {
            // Role comes from client request - easily manipulated!
            if (request.Role == "Admin")
            {
                _userService.UpdateUserAsAdmin(request.UserId, request.Data);
                return Ok("User updated with admin privileges");
            }

            _userService.UpdateUser(request.UserId, request.Data);
            return Ok("User updated");
        }

        // VULNERABLE: Uses client-provided user ID without ownership check
        [HttpGet("profile/{userId}")]
        public IActionResult GetProfile(int userId)
        {
            // Any authenticated user can access any profile!
            var profile = _userService.GetProfile(userId);
            return Ok(profile);
        }

        // VULNERABLE: Allows users to set their own role
        [HttpPost("set-role")]
        public IActionResult SetRole([FromBody] SetRoleRequest request)
        {
            _userService.SetUserRole(request.UserId, request.NewRole);
            return Ok($"Role set to {request.NewRole}");
        }
    }

    public class UserUpdateRequest
    {
        public int UserId { get; set; }
        public string Role { get; set; }
        public object Data { get; set; }
    }

    public class SetRoleRequest
    {
        public int UserId { get; set; }
        public string NewRole { get; set; }
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```json
{
  "userId": 123,
  "role": "Admin",
  "data": {"salary": 999999}
}
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Role information comes from the client request, which attackers can easily modify
- No server-side verification of the user's actual role from a trusted source
- Any user can escalate to admin privileges by simply changing the role parameter
- Horizontal privilege escalation: users can access other users' profiles
- Self-service role assignment allows complete privilege escalation

**SECURE VERSION**:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Security.Claims;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Logging;

namespace SecureApp.Controllers
{
    [ApiController]
    [Route("api/[controller]")]
    [Authorize] // Require authentication for all endpoints
    public class UserController : ControllerBase
    {
        private readonly IUserService _userService;
        private readonly ILogger<UserController> _logger;

        public UserController(IUserService userService, ILogger<UserController> logger)
        {
            _userService = userService;
            _logger = logger;
        }

        // SECURE: Role verified from server-side claims, not client input
        [HttpPost("update-user")]
        [Authorize(Roles = "Admin")] // Framework enforces role check
        public IActionResult UpdateUserAsAdmin([FromBody] AdminUserUpdateRequest request)
        {
            var adminId = GetCurrentUserId();
            _logger.LogInformation("Admin {AdminId} updating user {UserId}", adminId, request.UserId);

            _userService.UpdateUserAsAdmin(request.UserId, request.Data, adminId);
            return Ok("User updated with admin privileges");
        }

        // SECURE: Users can only access their own profile
        [HttpGet("profile")]
        public IActionResult GetOwnProfile()
        {
            var userId = GetCurrentUserId();
            var profile = _userService.GetProfile(userId);
            return Ok(profile);
        }

        // SECURE: Only super admins can set roles, with audit logging
        [HttpPost("set-role")]
        [Authorize(Roles = "SuperAdmin")]
        public IActionResult SetRole([FromBody] SetRoleRequest request)
        {
            var adminId = GetCurrentUserId();

            // Prevent privilege escalation to equal or higher roles
            if (!CanAssignRole(request.NewRole))
            {
                _logger.LogWarning("Privilege escalation attempt by {AdminId} to assign {Role}",
                    adminId, request.NewRole);
                return Forbid();
            }

            _userService.SetUserRole(request.UserId, request.NewRole, adminId);
            _logger.LogInformation("SuperAdmin {AdminId} set user {UserId} role to {Role}",
                adminId, request.UserId, request.NewRole);

            return Ok($"Role set to {request.NewRole}");
        }

        private int GetCurrentUserId()
        {
            var userIdClaim = User.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)?.Value;
            if (int.TryParse(userIdClaim, out int userId))
            {
                return userId;
            }
            throw new UnauthorizedAccessException("Invalid user identity");
        }

        private bool CanAssignRole(string targetRole)
        {
            // SuperAdmin can assign Admin or User roles, but not SuperAdmin
            var allowedRoles = new[] { "User", "Admin", "Moderator" };
            return Array.Exists(allowedRoles, r => 
                r.Equals(targetRole, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));
        }
    }

    public class AdminUserUpdateRequest
    {
        public int UserId { get; set; }
        public object Data { get; set; }
        // Note: No Role field - role comes from server-side claims
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")] attribute**: Framework-level role enforcement from authenticated claims, not client input
- **Server-side identity retrieval**: User ID comes from authenticated JWT/cookie claims, not request body
- **Role hierarchy enforcement**: SuperAdmins cannot assign SuperAdmin role, preventing self-elevation
- **Comprehensive audit logging**: All privileged actions logged with actor identity for forensics

For granular, resource-based authorization, you need policy-based authorization with custom requirements and handlers. This implements attribute-based access control (ABAC) which considers the resource context, not just the user's role.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Security.Claims;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Logging;

namespace ProductionApp.Authorization
{
    // Custom authorization requirement
    public class ResourceOwnerRequirement : IAuthorizationRequirement
    {
        public ResourceOwnerRequirement(bool allowDepartmentAccess = false)
        {
            AllowDepartmentAccess = allowDepartmentAccess;
        }

        public bool AllowDepartmentAccess { get; }
    }

    // Authorization handler with resource context
    public class ResourceOwnerHandler : AuthorizationHandler<ResourceOwnerRequirement, IResourceEntity>
    {
        private readonly IUserService _userService;
        private readonly ILogger<ResourceOwnerHandler> _logger;

        public ResourceOwnerHandler(IUserService userService, ILogger<ResourceOwnerHandler> logger)
        {
            _userService = userService;
            _logger = logger;
        }

        protected override async Task HandleRequirementAsync(
            AuthorizationHandlerContext context,
            ResourceOwnerRequirement requirement,
            IResourceEntity resource)
        {
            var userIdClaim = context.User.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)?.Value;
            if (!int.TryParse(userIdClaim, out int userId))
            {
                _logger.LogWarning("Authorization failed: Invalid user identity");
                context.Fail();
                return;
            }

            // Check 1: Is user the resource owner?
            if (resource.OwnerId == userId)
            {
                _logger.LogDebug("User {UserId} authorized as owner of resource {ResourceId}",
                    userId, resource.Id);
                context.Succeed(requirement);
                return;
            }

            // Check 2: Does user have department-level access?
            if (requirement.AllowDepartmentAccess)
            {
                var user = await _userService.GetUserAsync(userId);
                if (user.DepartmentId == resource.DepartmentId && 
                    user.HasPermission("department:read"))
                {
                    _logger.LogDebug("User {UserId} authorized via department access for resource {ResourceId}",
                        userId, resource.Id);
                    context.Succeed(requirement);
                    return;
                }
            }

            // Check 3: Is user a system admin?
            if (context.User.IsInRole("SystemAdmin"))
            {
                _logger.LogInformation("SystemAdmin {UserId} accessing resource {ResourceId}",
                    userId, resource.Id);
                context.Succeed(requirement);
                return;
            }

            _logger.LogWarning("Authorization denied: User {UserId} attempted to access resource {ResourceId}",
                userId, resource.Id);
            context.Fail();
        }
    }

    // Resource entity interface
    public interface IResourceEntity
    {
        int Id { get; }
        int OwnerId { get; }
        int DepartmentId { get; }
    }
}

namespace ProductionApp.Controllers
{
    using ProductionApp.Authorization;

    [ApiController]
    [Route("api/[controller]")]
    [Authorize]
    public class DocumentController : ControllerBase
    {
        private readonly IDocumentService _documentService;
        private readonly IAuthorizationService _authorizationService;
        private readonly ILogger<DocumentController> _logger;

        public DocumentController(
            IDocumentService documentService,
            IAuthorizationService authorizationService,
            ILogger<DocumentController> logger)
        {
            _documentService = documentService;
            _authorizationService = authorizationService;
            _logger = logger;
        }

        [HttpGet("{documentId}")]
        public async Task<IActionResult> GetDocument(int documentId)
        {
            var document = await _documentService.GetDocumentAsync(documentId);
            if (document == null)
            {
                return NotFound();
            }

            // Resource-based authorization check
            var authResult = await _authorizationService.AuthorizeAsync(
                User,
                document,
                new ResourceOwnerRequirement(allowDepartmentAccess: true));

            if (!authResult.Succeeded)
            {
                _logger.LogWarning("Unauthorized access attempt to document {DocumentId} by user {UserId}",
                    documentId, User.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)?.Value);
                return Forbid();
            }

            return Ok(document);
        }

        [HttpPut("{documentId}")]
        public async Task<IActionResult> UpdateDocument(int documentId, [FromBody] DocumentUpdateDto dto)
        {
            var document = await _documentService.GetDocumentAsync(documentId);
            if (document == null)
            {
                return NotFound();
            }

            // Stricter requirement for updates - owner only, no department access
            var authResult = await _authorizationService.AuthorizeAsync(
                User,
                document,
                new ResourceOwnerRequirement(allowDepartmentAccess: false));

            if (!authResult.Succeeded)
            {
                _logger.LogWarning("Unauthorized update attempt on document {DocumentId}",
                    documentId);
                return Forbid();
            }

            await _documentService.UpdateDocumentAsync(documentId, dto);
            return Ok();
        }

        [HttpDelete("{documentId}")]
        [Authorize(Policy = "RequireAdminOrOwner")]
        public async Task<IActionResult> DeleteDocument(int documentId)
        {
            var document = await _documentService.GetDocumentAsync(documentId);
            if (document == null)
            {
                return NotFound();
            }

            var userId = GetCurrentUserId();

            // Defense in depth: Additional ownership check even with policy
            if (document.OwnerId != userId && !User.IsInRole("SystemAdmin"))
            {
                _logger.LogCritical("Delete authorization bypass attempt! User {UserId}, Document {DocumentId}",
                    userId, documentId);
                return Forbid();
            }

            await _documentService.DeleteDocumentAsync(documentId, userId);
            _logger.LogInformation("Document {DocumentId} deleted by user {UserId}",
                documentId, userId);

            return NoContent();
        }

        private int GetCurrentUserId()
        {
            var claim = User.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)?.Value;
            return int.TryParse(claim, out int id) ? id : throw new UnauthorizedAccessException();
        }
    }
}

// Startup configuration
namespace ProductionApp
{
    using ProductionApp.Authorization;
    using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;

    public static class AuthorizationConfig
    {
        public static IServiceCollection AddAuthorizationPolicies(this IServiceCollection services)
        {
            services.AddAuthorization(options =>
            {
                // Default policy requires authenticated user
                options.DefaultPolicy = new AuthorizationPolicyBuilder()
                    .RequireAuthenticatedUser()
                    .Build();

                // Admin or owner policy for sensitive operations
                options.AddPolicy("RequireAdminOrOwner", policy =>
                    policy.RequireAssertion(context =>
                        context.User.IsInRole("SystemAdmin") ||
                        context.User.IsInRole("Admin")));

                // Require recent authentication for critical operations
                options.AddPolicy("RequireRecentAuth", policy =>
                    policy.RequireClaim("auth_time")
                          .RequireAssertion(context =>
                          {
                              var authTime = context.User.FindFirst("auth_time")?.Value;
                              if (long.TryParse(authTime, out long epoch))
                              {
                                  var authDateTime = DateTimeOffset.FromUnixTimeSeconds(epoch);
                                  return authDateTime > DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddMinutes(-15);
                              }
                              return false;
                          }));
            });

            // Register authorization handler
            services.AddScoped<IAuthorizationHandler, ResourceOwnerHandler>();

            return services;
        }
    }
}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Framework-level authentication**: JWT/Cookie validation before any code executes
```csharp
[Authorize] // Layer 1: Must be authenticated
public class SecureController : ControllerBase { }
```

2. **Policy-based authorization**: Custom requirements checked at endpoint level
```csharp
[Authorize(Policy = "RequireAdminOrOwner")] // Layer 2: Policy check
public async Task<IActionResult> SensitiveAction() { }
```

3. **Resource-based authorization**: Runtime check against actual resource
```csharp
// Layer 3: Check against the specific resource
var authResult = await _authorizationService.AuthorizeAsync(User, document, requirement);
if (!authResult.Succeeded) return Forbid();
```

4. **Defense in depth code validation**: Additional explicit checks even after policy passes
```csharp
// Layer 4: Belt-and-suspenders verification
if (document.OwnerId != userId && !User.IsInRole("SystemAdmin"))
{
    _logger.LogCritical("Authorization bypass attempt!");
    return Forbid();
}
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Audit logging at every authorization decision**: Failed and successful attempts logged with full context
- **Time-based authentication freshness**: Critical operations require recent login via auth_time claim
- **Hierarchical permission model**: Department access is additive permission, not a replacement for ownership
- **Fail-closed design**: Missing claims or parse failures result in authorization denial
- **Centralized policy configuration**: All policies defined in one place for easy security review
- **Separate read/write permissions**: Reading allows department access, writing requires ownership

Role-based access control (RBAC) is critical for protecting administrative functions, but many implementations are vulnerable to privilege escalation attacks where users can elevate their own permissions.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());

// VULNERABLE: Role stored in client-controlled JWT
app.post('/api/login', async (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;
  const user = await db.findUser(username);

  if (user && await bcrypt.compare(password, user.password)) {
    // DANGER: Role is included in JWT payload
    const token = jwt.sign(
      { userId: user.id, username: user.username, role: user.role },
      'secret-key',
      { expiresIn: '24h' }
    );
    res.json({ token });
  } else {
    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });
  }
});

// VULNERABLE: Trusts role from token without server-side verification
app.put('/api/users/:id/role', (req, res) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, 'secret-key');

  // DANGER: Only checks if user claims to be admin
  if (decoded.role === 'admin') {
    const { newRole } = req.body;
    db.updateUserRole(req.params.id, newRole);
    res.json({ success: true });
  } else {
    res.status(403).json({ error: 'Not authorized' });
  }
});

// VULNERABLE: User can update their own profile including role
app.put('/api/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, 'secret-key');

  // DANGER: No check on what fields can be updated
  if (decoded.userId === parseInt(req.params.id)) {
    db.updateUser(req.params.id, req.body); // Accepts ANY fields including 'role'
    res.json({ success: true });
  } else {
    res.status(403).json({ error: 'Not authorized' });
  }
});
```

**Attack Payload**:
```bash
# Attacker modifies their own profile to escalate privileges
curl -X PUT http://api.example.com/api/users/123 \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <valid_user_token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"role": "admin", "name": "Regular User"}'

# Or forge a new JWT with elevated role (if secret is weak/leaked)
curl -X PUT http://api.example.com/api/users/456/role \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <forged_admin_token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"newRole": "admin"}'
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Role stored in JWT can be forged if secret is compromised
- No server-side verification of actual user role from database
- Profile update endpoint accepts arbitrary fields including sensitive 'role' field
- Mass assignment vulnerability allows privilege escalation

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const crypto = require('crypto');
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());

const JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET; // Strong secret from environment
const ALLOWED_PROFILE_FIELDS = ['name', 'email', 'avatar', 'bio'];

// SECURE: JWT only contains user ID, role fetched server-side
app.post('/api/login', async (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;
  const user = await db.findUser(username);

  if (user && await bcrypt.compare(password, user.password)) {
    // Only include user ID in token, NOT the role
    const token = jwt.sign(
      { userId: user.id, jti: crypto.randomUUID() },
      JWT_SECRET,
      { expiresIn: '1h' }
    );
    res.json({ token });
  } else {
    await logFailedLogin(username, req.ip);
    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });
  }
});

// SECURE: Middleware that fetches role from database
const authenticate = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
    if (!token) return res.status(401).json({ error: 'No token provided' });

    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET);

    // CRITICAL: Fetch current role from database, don't trust JWT
    const user = await db.findUserById(decoded.userId);
    if (!user || user.isDisabled) {
      return res.status(401).json({ error: 'User not found or disabled' });
    }

    req.user = { id: user.id, role: user.role, permissions: user.permissions };
    next();
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid token' });
  }
};

// SECURE: Role-based authorization middleware
const requireRole = (...allowedRoles) => {
  return (req, res, next) => {
    if (!allowedRoles.includes(req.user.role)) {
      auditLog.warn('Unauthorized access attempt', {
        userId: req.user.id,
        requiredRoles: allowedRoles,
        userRole: req.user.role,
        endpoint: req.originalUrl
      });
      return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Insufficient permissions' });
    }
    next();
  };
};

// SECURE: Only admins can change roles, with audit logging
app.put('/api/users/:id/role', authenticate, requireRole('admin'), async (req, res) => {
  const { newRole } = req.body;
  const targetUserId = parseInt(req.params.id);

  // Prevent self-demotion of last admin
  const adminCount = await db.countAdmins();
  if (req.user.id === targetUserId && req.user.role === 'admin' && adminCount === 1) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Cannot remove last admin' });
  }

  await db.updateUserRole(targetUserId, newRole);

  auditLog.info('Role changed', {
    changedBy: req.user.id,
    targetUser: targetUserId,
    newRole: newRole,
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
  });

  res.json({ success: true });
});

// SECURE: Whitelist allowed fields for profile updates
app.put('/api/users/:id', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
  const targetUserId = parseInt(req.params.id);

  // Users can only update their own profile
  if (req.user.id !== targetUserId && req.user.role !== 'admin') {
    return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Cannot modify other users' });
  }

  // CRITICAL: Only allow whitelisted fields
  const sanitizedUpdate = {};
  for (const field of ALLOWED_PROFILE_FIELDS) {
    if (req.body[field] !== undefined) {
      sanitizedUpdate[field] = req.body[field];
    }
  }

  await db.updateUser(targetUserId, sanitizedUpdate);
  res.json({ success: true });
});
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Server-side role verification**: Role is always fetched from database, never trusted from JWT
- **Field whitelisting**: Only explicitly allowed fields can be updated, preventing mass assignment
- **Separation of concerns**: Role changes require admin privileges through separate endpoint
- **Audit logging**: All privilege-related actions are logged for forensic analysis

Hierarchical and resource-based permissions are common in enterprise applications but introduce additional privilege escalation vectors. You need attribute-based access control (ABAC) combined with strict hierarchy enforcement.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const crypto = require('crypto');
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
const { createLogger, transports, format } = require('winston');

const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

// Audit logger for security events
const auditLogger = createLogger({
  level: 'info',
  format: format.combine(format.timestamp(), format.json()),
  transports: [
    new transports.File({ filename: 'audit.log' }),
    new transports.Console()
  ]
});

// Role hierarchy - higher index = more privileges
const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {
  'viewer': 0,
  'contributor': 1,
  'editor': 2,
  'moderator': 3,
  'admin': 4,
  'superadmin': 5
};

// Permission matrix per resource type
const PERMISSIONS = {
  document: {
    read: ['viewer', 'contributor', 'editor', 'moderator', 'admin', 'superadmin'],
    write: ['contributor', 'editor', 'moderator', 'admin', 'superadmin'],
    delete: ['moderator', 'admin', 'superadmin'],
    share: ['editor', 'moderator', 'admin', 'superadmin']
  },
  user: {
    read: ['moderator', 'admin', 'superadmin'],
    write: ['admin', 'superadmin'],
    delete: ['superadmin'],
    changeRole: ['admin', 'superadmin']
  },
  settings: {
    read: ['admin', 'superadmin'],
    write: ['superadmin']
  }
};

// Rate limiting for sensitive operations
const privilegedRateLimiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000,
  max: 10,
  message: { error: 'Too many privileged operations, try again later' },
  standardHeaders: true
});

class AccessControl {
  constructor() {
    this.permissionCache = new Map();
  }

  // Get role level for hierarchy comparison
  getRoleLevel(role) {
    return ROLE_HIERARCHY[role] ?? -1;
  }

  // Check if actor can modify target's role
  canChangeRole(actorRole, targetCurrentRole, targetNewRole) {
    const actorLevel = this.getRoleLevel(actorRole);
    const currentLevel = this.getRoleLevel(targetCurrentRole);
    const newLevel = this.getRoleLevel(targetNewRole);

    // CRITICAL: Cannot escalate to same or higher level than yourself
    if (newLevel >= actorLevel) {
      return { allowed: false, reason: 'Cannot grant role equal to or higher than your own' };
    }

    // CRITICAL: Cannot modify users at same or higher level
    if (currentLevel >= actorLevel) {
      return { allowed: false, reason: 'Cannot modify users at your level or above' };
    }

    // Must have changeRole permission for user resource
    if (!PERMISSIONS.user.changeRole.includes(actorRole)) {
      return { allowed: false, reason: 'Insufficient permission to change roles' };
    }

    return { allowed: true };
  }

  // Check resource-level permission
  async canAccess(user, resourceType, action, resourceId = null) {
    // Check basic role permission
    const allowedRoles = PERMISSIONS[resourceType]?.[action];
    if (!allowedRoles || !allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {
      return { allowed: false, reason: 'Role does not have this permission' };
    }

    // Check resource-specific permissions (ownership, sharing, etc.)
    if (resourceId) {
      const resourceAccess = await this.checkResourceAccess(user, resourceType, resourceId, action);
      if (!resourceAccess.allowed) {
        return resourceAccess;
      }
    }

    return { allowed: true };
  }

  async checkResourceAccess(user, resourceType, resourceId, action) {
    const resource = await db.getResource(resourceType, resourceId);
    if (!resource) {
      return { allowed: false, reason: 'Resource not found' };
    }

    // Owner always has access (unless it's a system resource)
    if (resource.ownerId === user.id && !resource.isSystemResource) {
      return { allowed: true };
    }

    // Check explicit sharing/grants
    const grant = await db.getResourceGrant(resourceType, resourceId, user.id);
    if (grant && grant.permissions.includes(action)) {
      return { allowed: true };
    }

    // Check team/organization access
    if (resource.teamId && user.teams?.includes(resource.teamId)) {
      const teamRole = await db.getTeamRole(user.id, resource.teamId);
      if (this.teamRoleCanPerform(teamRole, action)) {
        return { allowed: true };
      }
    }

    // Admins can access based on role, but log it
    if (this.getRoleLevel(user.role) >= ROLE_HIERARCHY.admin) {
      auditLogger.warn('Admin override access', {
        userId: user.id,
        resourceType,
        resourceId,
        action
      });
      return { allowed: true, adminOverride: true };
    }

    return { allowed: false, reason: 'No access to this resource' };
  }

  teamRoleCanPerform(teamRole, action) {
    const teamPermissions = {
      member: ['read'],
      contributor: ['read', 'write'],
      maintainer: ['read', 'write', 'delete', 'share']
    };
    return teamPermissions[teamRole]?.includes(action) ?? false;
  }
}

const accessControl = new AccessControl();

// Authentication middleware
const authenticate = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
    if (!token) {
      return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Authentication required' });
    }

    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);
    const user = await db.findUserById(decoded.userId);

    if (!user || user.isDisabled || user.isLocked) {
      auditLogger.warn('Access attempt by disabled/locked user', {
        userId: decoded.userId,
        ip: req.ip
      });
      return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Account is disabled' });
    }

    // Check for session invalidation (logout, password change)
    const tokenIssuedAt = decoded.iat * 1000;
    if (user.tokenInvalidatedAt && tokenIssuedAt < user.tokenInvalidatedAt) {
      return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Session expired, please login again' });
    }

    req.user = {
      id: user.id,
      role: user.role,
      teams: user.teams,
      permissions: user.customPermissions
    };
    next();
  } catch (error) {
    auditLogger.error('Authentication error', { error: error.message, ip: req.ip });
    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid authentication' });
  }
};

// Authorization middleware factory
const authorize = (resourceType, action) => {
  return async (req, res, next) => {
    const resourceId = req.params.id || req.params.resourceId;
    const accessResult = await accessControl.canAccess(
      req.user,
      resourceType,
      action,
      resourceId
    );

    if (!accessResult.allowed) {
      auditLogger.warn('Authorization denied', {
        userId: req.user.id,
        userRole: req.user.role,
        resourceType,
        action,
        resourceId,
        reason: accessResult.reason,
        ip: req.ip
      });
      return res.status(403).json({ error: accessResult.reason });
    }

    if (accessResult.adminOverride) {
      res.set('X-Admin-Override', 'true');
    }

    next();
  };
};

// SECURE: Role change with hierarchy enforcement
app.put('/api/users/:id/role',
  authenticate,
  privilegedRateLimiter,
  authorize('user', 'changeRole'),
  async (req, res) => {
    const targetUserId = parseInt(req.params.id);
    const { newRole } = req.body;

    // Validate new role exists
    if (!(newRole in ROLE_HIERARCHY)) {
      return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid role' });
    }

    // Prevent self-modification
    if (req.user.id === targetUserId) {
      auditLogger.warn('Self role modification attempt', {
        userId: req.user.id,
        attemptedRole: newRole
      });
      return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Cannot modify your own role' });
    }

    const targetUser = await db.findUserById(targetUserId);
    if (!targetUser) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });
    }

    // Check hierarchy constraints
    const hierarchyCheck = accessControl.canChangeRole(
      req.user.role,
      targetUser.role,
      newRole
    );

    if (!hierarchyCheck.allowed) {
      auditLogger.warn('Privilege escalation attempt blocked', {
        actorId: req.user.id,
        actorRole: req.user.role,
        targetUserId,
        targetCurrentRole: targetUser.role,
        attemptedNewRole: newRole,
        reason: hierarchyCheck.reason
      });
      return res.status(403).json({ error: hierarchyCheck.reason });
    }

    // Require confirmation for privilege changes
    const confirmationToken = req.headers['x-confirmation-token'];
    const expectedToken = await db.getConfirmationToken(req.user.id, 'roleChange');
    if (!confirmationToken || confirmationToken !== expectedToken) {
      // Generate and send confirmation token
      const token = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');
      await db.storeConfirmationToken(req.user.id, 'roleChange', token, 5 * 60 * 1000);
      return res.status(428).json({
        error: 'Confirmation required',
        message: 'Please confirm this action',
        confirmationRequired: true
      });
    }

    // Execute role change
    await db.updateUserRole(targetUserId, newRole);
    await db.invalidateConfirmationToken(req.user.id, 'roleChange');

    // Invalidate target user's sessions
    await db.invalidateUserSessions(targetUserId);

    auditLogger.info('Role changed successfully', {
      changedBy: req.user.id,
      changedByRole: req.user.role,
      targetUser: targetUserId,
      previousRole: targetUser.role,
      newRole: newRole,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
      ip: req.ip
    });

    res.json({ success: true, message: `User role changed to ${newRole}` });
  }
);

// SECURE: Resource access with owner/sharing checks
app.delete('/api/documents/:id',
  authenticate,
  authorize('document', 'delete'),
  async (req, res) => {
    const documentId = req.params.id;

    // Soft delete with audit trail
    await db.softDeleteDocument(documentId, req.user.id);

    auditLogger.info('Document deleted', {
      documentId,
      deletedBy: req.user.id,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    });

    res.json({ success: true });
  }
);

app.listen(3000);
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Role Hierarchy Enforcement**:
```javascript
// Users can NEVER grant roles equal to or higher than their own
if (newLevel >= actorLevel) {
  return { allowed: false, reason: 'Cannot grant role equal to or higher than your own' };
}
```

2. **Resource-Level Access Control**:
```javascript
// Check ownership, explicit grants, and team membership
const grant = await db.getResourceGrant(resourceType, resourceId, user.id);
if (grant && grant.permissions.includes(action)) {
  return { allowed: true };
}
```

3. **Confirmation for Sensitive Operations**:
```javascript
// Require explicit confirmation for privilege changes
const confirmationToken = req.headers['x-confirmation-token'];
if (!confirmationToken || confirmationToken !== expectedToken) {
  return res.status(428).json({ confirmationRequired: true });
}
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Session invalidation on role change**: Prevents continued access with old privileges after demotion
- **Self-modification prevention**: Users cannot change their own role, even admins
- **Rate limiting on privileged operations**: Prevents brute-force privilege escalation attempts
- **Comprehensive audit logging**: All access decisions and privilege changes are logged with context
- **Admin override tracking**: When admins bypass normal access controls, it's explicitly logged and flagged

Role management is extremely sensitive functionality that requires strict authorization controls. Many applications have been compromised due to improper privilege escalation protections.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import javax.servlet.http.*;
import java.sql.*;
import com.google.gson.Gson;

public class UserRoleController extends HttpServlet {
